The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 220 players in fray

OUR CORRESPONDENT

Jamshedpur: The Jamshedpur leg of The Telegraph Schools Chess Championship, for students across Bihar and Jharkhand, was inaugurated on Saturday at the JRD Tata Sports Complex. 

The week-long event, which will conclude on October 21, is being organised by Tata Steel in association with East Singhbhum District Chess Association (ESDCA) and Alekhine Chess Club, Calcutta and is sponsored by Linc. 

A total of 220 players from different schools in Bihar and Jharkhand will fight for the top five slots to get an entry into the finals in Calcutta later this year. Of the 220 contestants, about 50 are from Bihar. 

The tournament has been divided into 11 rounds as per FIDE rules. The five categories in which the contestants will participate are under-six, under-eight, under-10, under-12 and under-14. 

The best youngest player award will be given to the contestant who scores maximum point among both boys and girls. The secretary of ESDCA, R. S. Prasad, informed that the winner will bag a cash award of Rs 4,000. The second, third, fourth and fifth prize winners will be richer by Rs 3,000, 2,000, 1,000 and 500, respectively. 

There will be a special trophy for the winner and runner-up. There will be a cash prize of Rs 400 each to those securing sixth to 10th place and Rs 300 for those securing 11th to 15th position. There will also be consolation prize of Rs 200 each to the best boys and girls under different age categories. 




